children.text: The diagonal speedbracing that runs across the tops of the trusses has not been fixed to the wall top plates at an angle less than 45 degrees, and the alternative fixing detail at the top plate has not been adopted.

The relevant Australian Standard, AS 4440 Installation of Nail-Plated Timber Roof Trusses, clause 4.3.8 Fixing, provides a detail outlining the method for connecting speedbrace to the top plate at the heel;
The fixing of the speedbracing must be rectified in accordance with Australian Standard AS 4440, or if this method is not achievable, then the alterative heel fixing detail shown above must be used.
